  "text": "Using the two consensus-based frameworks of the ESPEN Special Interest Group [CITATION_1] and Fearon et al. [CITATION_2] , we classified pre-cachexia in nine patients (23 %) and cachexia in seven patients (18 %). The remaining twenty-four patients were classified as no-cachexia patients ( Table 2) . None of the patients met the criteria of refractory cancer cachexia: measurements were carried out at diagnosis, just before starting anticancer treatment, and the Karnofsky performance score was relatively high (70-100) and the expected survival was at least 3 months in all patients.",
